                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/888a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-06T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 6, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. As a result of conversations in Washington with the representatives of the
                    other neutral governments, the following note has been drawn up which has been
                    submitted to those Governments for their comment and suggestions. Do not
                    transmit this to the Bolivian Government until you receive further specific
                    instructions to do so.</p>
                <p>[Here follows the text of the note transmitted in telegram No. 536, December 6, 4
                    p.m., to the Chargé in Mexico, printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
